00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:05.520 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>We're in Milan at the Salone del Mobile,</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>the world's largest furniture fair.</i></c>

4cf2295d6f6e4aff98f6dcb109f033b1
00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:08.480 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>In 2025, there's a lot to see in Milan.</i></c>

32d91fa90d8944a7ba05970366b493eb
00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:14.000 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>–This is big.</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>–If you like design, you have to be here.</i></c>

407f804f85e34b768e2d29106809f25e
00:00:22.480 --> 00:00:27.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Nordic design has conquered the world
for over a hundred years.</c>

6665bf51f2604591995dd7e804e8d0fd
00:00:31.880 --> 00:00:33.520 align:left position:22%
I fell in love right away.

f94dc196f8724031b6c3700c116a5629
00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:36.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>All rooms with this: Wow!</c>

6c15965ad30e4f86b6f6c631344950a7
00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:39.400 align:left position:22%
I can't take furniture to heaven.

cfa1fa4b1f904bc18be2b329281385c6
00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:43.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But what exactly makes Nordic design–</c>

61cd85bbad2c439d8358ce66c3bcd25c
00:00:43.560 --> 00:00:46.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–enchant collectors
from all over the world?</c>

e26ce06385224c319856893a464186fb
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:54.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That wooden chairs and plastic chairs are sold
for fantastic sums internationally.</c>

5ac3484223c6474487531e0ab0984dbb
00:00:55.960 --> 00:01:02.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>From modest everyday objects to
immortal cultural icons–</c>

5a725fb87835425f8e6f083de7fc6bbc
00:01:02.680 --> 00:01:07.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–seen in movies
and in the most exclusive homes in the world.</c>

0a6abd731fbe4e308291b57625684962
00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:14.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This is a series
about a hundred years of Nordic design–</c>

799157a629f54c9aaf5d2068ad4379eb
00:01:14.560 --> 00:01:18.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and why it looks the way it does.</c>

2139d60236d44806b444b3e3cfca880a
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:42.680 align:left position:22%
There are fairs in London,
Copenhagen, Stockholm and Tokyo–

799c358ef6394847a12c62c8b93248d1
00:01:42.840 --> 00:01:49.760 align:left position:22%
–but always Milan
is the most important venue.

0fbbe62d1d384cefb2bcd05bf8edda3b
00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:55.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>At the world's largest design fair
in Milan–</c>

5a5dfa3dafbe499495037f7dd56d27b9
00:01:55.400 --> 00:02:01.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–the latest absolute
in design and form is shown.</c>

b610ecb0f5b14e27904d41c5abb43675
00:02:01.520 --> 00:02:09.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Thousands of exhibitors from
all over the world compete for attention.</c>

1182b7c992f34454a8574f3f17e0a93f
00:02:13.120 --> 00:02:19.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And one of them is the lighting designer
Norwegian Daniel Rybakken.</c>

4a54f8e80c454dfa9aa4ff14d168a830
00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:25.200 align:left position:22%
Milan is the most important fair for me, and where I began my career.

d897f1de95e540d6909dd2e0427a0858
00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:29.240 align:left position:22%
It is where I grew up
as a designer.

11122e8e7fb44f70ac6f2c56b897c2cc
00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:33.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Daniel Rybakken is
one of the designers of the 2000s–</c>

fe92347f071f4d4b9a467707aa0d68eb
00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:38.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–who wants to break
with all previous conventions.</c>

7cfced3bd6234c53bd7f3d93b81b3631
00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:43.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His lamps don't look at all like
how lamps are supposed to look–</c>

05bb57f2d3bf41bcaee68fd5c81f53fd
00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:47.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but are imitations
of Nordic sunlight.</c>

c84701d28cde43b6a1356f48038f35ce
00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:52.480 align:left position:22%
A Scandinavian or Nordic light–

2160681db7b94224b2e6865f52f09fcc
00:02:52.640 --> 00:02:59.440 align:left position:22%
–that ranges from
very diffuse light to sharp.

377c492ce3f74aa2857f9e0fda19570a
00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:04.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Daniel Rybakken's lamps break
with the formal tradition–</c>

d8bb856a977d4d9b8456691a245841a1
00:03:04.360 --> 00:03:09.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but also aspire
to the authentic, the natural.</c>

52200a2a8b5e42f3992bb14118bf78f9
00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:15.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And it fits perfectly
with the trends of this year's fair.</c>

fcc0ccf84eea4fe6b2b88ae912e8698a
00:03:16.800 --> 00:03:21.440 align:left position:22%
Some directions become clearer–

2e8a9597b10647b0aaeb291eef6319f1
00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:29.280 align:left position:22%
–like that sustainability is not just
about reusable materials more.

a1929d47b3bb47e3a69b4c95750b518e
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:34.000 align:left position:22%
Another trend is
that craftsmanship is coming back.

ed1fac022f5948f7bee4fb808489f4e7
00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:40.120 align:left position:22%
We want to be able to feel the surfaces and materials.

84a5673289134d6884ec97d4c4633aec
00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:43.400 align:left position:22%
And see the hand of a person.

ca1d200194684acb9538ee8ff7aa683a
00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:58.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The millennium begins with a catastrophe
that never happened – the millennium bug.</c>

6e59f59febad4c54a1d24c75580e9458
00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:05.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The one that was feared would crash
the world's computers never came.</c>

6727d3acf70c498d925aab6ec41577a8
00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:13.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But to say that the 2000 was
free from catastrophes would be a lie.</c>

704fa026b7294491b9a928383c56dadd
00:04:14.200 --> 00:04:18.840 align:left position:22%
The economic recession
continued for three years.

8bd179a0ff8d4558b05bf621f0ca7ccd
00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:21.680 align:left position:22%
I want you to feel panic.

85fc56f9f8184fef8f0f2b1e8305e659
00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:24.880 align:left position:22%
Act as if your house is on fire.

bc6bb285ec3b4d5d9babb883999723a1
00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:26.760 align:left position:22%
Only time.

e42f437719a044b293d5955032db77b3
00:04:26.920 --> 00:04:31.440 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>...previously protested this year</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>for a better climate.</i></c>

5bd845f1e03347cd844283ed3d416e9b
00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:35.600 align:left position:22%
Much snow but still talk
about global warming!

02cc2e8fea9042c79678f753e00d6ed
00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:40.480 align:left position:22%
How can global warming exist
when it's so cold?

5518f27870f94b1db35725669388b287
00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:49.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Designers in the new millennium
must reinvent the craft.</c>

5ffbea87c2904c68a762e2d28bb131e8
00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:53.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Now design can be
a matter–</c>

5ef217e1c12d44999ac914a9fcd88394
00:04:53.640 --> 00:04:55.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–war against conventions–</c>

4e6b512085a74b618204d0869cd7d42c
00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:01.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–or an exploration of new
materials to reduce the climate footprint.</c>

3cfca4ce314847ab85a651f84fa3d9a6
00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:08.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Why else do mushroom chairs arise
in a laboratory in Denmark?</c>

dd9c445813c64d6e82ceef5f867bc876
00:05:10.400 --> 00:05:17.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And what does a metal chair from Iceland say
about the Utøya attack?</c>

37c06354d5f44580b02cc762c420fce5
00:05:18.040 --> 00:05:22.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And why can't Madonna
and other celebrities–</c>

c2bc4c1bf04a44629aa288b88d592a9c
00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:25.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–separate from a Swedish horse lamp?</c>

07c00e31f65c4559a64a3f6d674b64b6
00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:08.800 align:left position:22%
Can we save the world?

058399f2882b407388c70aecba17bf4f
00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:13.160 align:left position:22%
I think it's difficult for humans.

52b74a386a7547f798955f421418998f
00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:20.920 align:left position:22%
We can create the best possible situation,
so that everyone can have a good life.

b3621f1e136341e99a78da4cdc02e0c2
00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:25.280 align:left position:22%
That's what design is.

fa7583c8042643239b6a54ebbf112bf8
00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:32.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In the sea just outside Copenhagen
blows every night–</c>

fe7a3442b545434487c62c30c9a8a622
00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:37.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–an apparently inexhaustible amount
of seaweed towards the shore–</c>

34314cbf6bda49569540327fc7fe6327
00:06:38.040 --> 00:06:43.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–directly towards the studio
of designer Jonas Edvard.</c>

df1708a912da466bb65e9c6975fa68e5
00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:48.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And in his hands
seaweed can become anything.</c>

52dc412f965c4bc0aad722b33fb90e4b
00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:56.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>As lighting
over mussels and seaweed–</c>

5c70b8c17ee146d1940686ebe0fa6195
00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:00.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–in one of the
finest restaurants in the North.</c>

c2cf0e0e56954ee9835f4657257ba264
00:07:05.080 --> 00:07:11.720 align:left position:22%
I work with unconventional materials,
but they are natural materials.

4c5adf5c221c406aae390000aa5194cb
00:07:11.880 --> 00:07:16.600 align:left position:22%
I got into this
because I'm interested in–

b02554c4c36c4a1191b5bf61cd9fff95
00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:23.600 align:left position:22%
–how we can create design
from natural materials in our immediate environment.

5ac5916148f24475a7f840d937f94b83
00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:37.080 align:left position:22%
I have found several types of seaweed,
mainly marine algae.

347a4b6390f84667ae854983ae3a2e83
00:07:37.240 --> 00:07:41.480 align:left position:22%
They have bubbles and can float on the surface.

ecdefe87b93944a593bee51d841c8250
00:07:41.640 --> 00:07:47.760 align:left position:22%
They also have sugar seaweed that
grows further away and doesn't float in as often.

91dc737f532f4bb6ad6fb31d18cdcf5c
00:07:52.280 --> 00:07:57.440 align:left position:22%
We have a lot of seaweed.
We have a coastline of 850 miles.

dd2afd7d916a4497859ddfab7b6d54c1
00:07:57.600 --> 00:08:01.560 align:left position:22%
It's a long coastline for the country's size.

7c9dfcd6a6104f8180268f54659cbc39
00:08:02.520 --> 00:08:07.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Seaweed, which in many people's opinion
is useless and smelly–</c>

45eec9492b6445129843f732a8092403
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:12.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is for Jonas Edvard
a resistant and untapped material.</c>

3e35591eeb214237a681ae1c0f028a07
00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:18.440 align:left position:22%
And we can harvest and use it.

a597678ee6944b3f80fd141891c55eb7
00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:24.560 align:left position:22%
Seaweed contains a binder
that can bind to paper among other things.

854641abe89b4f308738e4b02836ff9d
00:08:24.720 --> 00:08:28.120 align:left position:22%
It has always been used as a binder.

b52d663438bf4f57810f907d201117c3
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:41.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But using seaweed
is for Jonas Edvard much more–</c>

42ffffb32fb743dfb41fde0c7c7aca7b
00:08:41.320 --> 00:08:47.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–than working with a natural material,
free and resistant.</c>

d66b84336b6449b2b0377eea29c5beca
00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:55.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is also an endless story.</c>

3acf3d0fa21f41f8b10e83fadc16634d
00:09:01.960 --> 00:09:06.040 align:left position:22%
This story is not about us–

5d2b82fb541f41c68e00f53b991605c8
00:09:06.200 --> 00:09:09.800 align:left position:22%
–or what I want with my design.

039bc06908834b9fb8430eda719861db
00:09:09.960 --> 00:09:14.320 align:left position:22%
What can it contribute,
and how should we relate?

b913977cf77f409db54d42205cd8ccf6
00:09:14.480 --> 00:09:18.280 align:left position:22%
About our obligation to do the right thing.

45d7a20aaf7a452c8df1fe25926188b7
00:09:18.440 --> 00:09:24.040 align:left position:22%
What can be reused,
recycled or composted?

182202c82504431eaec41f52ef006013
00:10:04.080 --> 00:10:11.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Jonas Edvard grew up in the society
of abundance of the 80s and 90s–</c>

8e9a345b1fe2406e8f8464d10a701081
00:10:11.240 --> 00:10:17.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–when no one talked about sustainability
or limited natural resources.</c>

c800a8dac4d94a5d8d6b1933dc803c53
00:10:17.720 --> 00:10:24.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And he learned to design objects
from already existing materials.</c>

22e42b3b9ebc406e94dc0934376635ac
00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:34.120 align:left position:22%
Now it has become a mass or clay–

d45a83e5d3554aabb78a2e55e82e8020
00:10:34.280 --> 00:10:38.000 align:left position:22%
–that I can now press into a shape.

917ca90bf6554ea8a802b91749b8876a
00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:43.320 align:left position:22%
I have made a mold
into which the material fits.

9112f03cb724402792c7a4d337068a51
00:11:33.520 --> 00:11:39.560 align:left position:22%
All the materials I work with
are interesting in their original form.

1b9237330a54405e8c399ab6686b67b5
00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:44.760 align:left position:22%
I can find them like that.
I can find excavated lime.

8a60c35fac8641fbb1155055c39ddcea
00:11:44.920 --> 00:11:49.040 align:left position:22%
I can find seaweed
and living mushrooms.

f89cb75ab40b453fab33ef6856000d93
00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:48.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>From seaweed and mushrooms
Jonas Edvard creates new design.</c>

88fe1a25c6854ca192da1cb773926486
00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:53.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The materials are like a colleague
with a will of their own.</c>

d4d3d745f0664f16bd3ed6e4f94ec285
00:12:53.480 --> 00:12:59.240 align:left position:22%
When I work with mushrooms
I collaborate with something living.

0d0671e18c674d239db07ab585bf4e2c
00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:05.640 align:left position:22%
It is inspiring to have an organism
that manages well on its own.

fa086ec8d6c34624a680bf9c1cc201d9
00:13:05.800 --> 00:13:12.120 align:left position:22%
It is interesting to see how the mycelium
binds and becomes part of itself.

444c41368a844b78940e63d9182ed78b
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:20.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Jonas Edvard's design has eternal life.</c>

0369755131144eeb95c6de655cb37c31
00:13:21.080 --> 00:13:25.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>At least if eternal life
means that furniture and lamps–</c>

5ced15a4d473422caa5381f36aa60954
00:13:25.720 --> 00:13:30.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–when no longer used, can
decompose to their original form.</c>

3d6632cc9d7c40558e135ebf97586911
00:13:32.360 --> 00:13:38.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The mushroom chair that Edvard cultivated would be
disappeared after 60 days–</c>

3cb5063ddf19418a95eca7c421607117
00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:41.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–if left outdoors.</c>

fac45414a98a41ddaa1570479c4e1400
00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:47.320 align:left position:22%
The chair in the museum is fused from mushroom plates.

7a9df2a1c3754ce598062933850fd735
00:13:47.480 --> 00:13:51.280 align:left position:22%
It is made of plates that have grown together.

8f7207b834f246b8aa69440744ad2a73
00:13:51.440 --> 00:13:55.240 align:left position:22%
He was interested in scaling.

925e1997970f49ffa8916c11604c2a2e
00:13:55.400 --> 00:14:01.120 align:left position:22%
Can it be from a very small scale
to something functional?

9202e3a91be3460d80390c2d729cd0c2
00:14:01.280 --> 00:14:07.080 align:left position:22%
It can be sat on,
but it was a larger experiment.

eda48b6bece144ef8696461280a11120
00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:12.160 align:left position:22%
It took a long time and was difficult,
but it worked and was exciting.

54c7e778cce34d1f81ec9e39940993ed
00:14:12.320 --> 00:14:16.120 align:left position:22%
It is uncertain
working with something living.

90c2e29a9c3042e6a7f5e669dc4c5343
00:14:16.280 --> 00:14:19.680 align:left position:22%
Where does it go? Can it grow here?

62667ce80ad9417bbc7766357427d13f
00:14:19.840 --> 00:14:23.240 align:left position:22%
One becomes a farmer, not a designer.

699565cbac084876bec98a6b77ec9932
00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:30.200 align:left position:22%
One becomes an observer and collaborates
with a process one does not control.

76d0c12e62c9402eb9afd6cfa63570e8
00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:36.280 align:left position:22%
I can adjust the air humidity and temperature,
but I don't know where it leads.

45ee372b40034ec38b7ee5ffd365d4b0
00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:58.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The seaweed from the Baltic Sea
is now lamp shades–</c>

2dd7683df60e44f58f500936422f7b78
00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:05.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–illuminating the tables
of the Michelin-starred restaurant Noma in Copenhagen.</c>

6c7b71e2f2814ff497aca370a4555095
00:15:10.640 --> 00:15:16.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When the lamps no longer work,
they become compost for tomato cultivation.</c>

00ec40f03ee64fbaa9e8dd8bf3e0ecd5
00:15:20.160 --> 00:15:24.800 align:left position:22%
We don't save the world,
but we take one day at a time.

0f441f62ba234715afb56160c891cdf1
00:15:24.960 --> 00:15:31.720 align:left position:22%
We won't dominate the world in millions of years, or less–

18852867350a4077a13b267461220443
00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:34.800 align:left position:22%
–so we must do the best we can, now.

0bee2d621fb442888c3f7bc0dafb9d64
00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:47.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The Milan fair has grown considerably
since its inception in the early 60s.</c>

6ed693b721ad4a0583d5a9018723b7b4
00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:50.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The fair is in its 63rd year–</c>

507501960c394893b3287d79a68b9852
00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:55.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and has more than 2,000 exhibitors
from 37 countries.</c>

f15cbd1b807d4d159a9a7c846762c329
00:15:56.240 --> 00:16:03.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Many Nordic designers have used
Milan as their window to the world.</c>

1b85410855424ad4a80bfe5089eb7032
00:16:03.200 --> 00:16:06.240 align:left position:22%
Nordic design has an interesting role–

a75c89d45180447abc24f54109c1b3c5
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:13.360 align:left position:22%
–for the fair that began as a national fair
with mostly Italian exhibitors.

57949dc604c94277bbd806178d15bcb4
00:16:13.520 --> 00:16:17.400 align:left position:22%
Then it grew to become a global phenomenon.

713a6f057a214a33a732c2d08aba696f
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:22.880 align:left position:22%
Italian craftsmanship
has always been appreciated in the North.

b720ed84ebdd43ea9191a860450a1fe7
00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:29.640 align:left position:22%
We have the same respect for materials.

0219da693da544c8b7115a94a8d1d149
00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:33.000 align:left position:22%
Nordic design and Nordic companies–

b82fb061005c4844a879468508928130
00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:40.000 align:left position:22%
–had an important role in making our fair
so international.

c9da6ed4f0104a6fbf1966ebc231c7ce
00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:48.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When we exhibited in Milan
we brought moss and branches–</c>

85b78786b33a4ebdadf7ae5ac5d51134
00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:55.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and hid the things among what we had
collected from the forest. It looked good.</c>

d674a13bffea4940947d929c3cb4e1df
00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:32.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When you were little the forest was a place
where you built for yourself.</c>

34e8672d96954aaf8d3e20e5c6869a03
00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:36.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>You made things. You found something
that looked like a sofa in the forest.</c>

0232f96ace5e455d97375fb54babeb79
00:17:36.520 --> 00:17:39.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>You inhabited the forest.</c>

524b683c62f74896b5e9949d583fe308
00:17:43.720 --> 00:17:47.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>So you played all day,
and it looked like...</c>

56d2f08b4111447a97fecf655c7f8b36
00:17:47.880 --> 00:17:50.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>You could climb something in a tree–</c>

bda5688a43694c10a406ec8ac207c476
00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:56.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and it became the children's playground
for weeks.</c>

8fbaa7b0b9d24e65b31291dc38824f9
00:18:20.760 --> 00:18:26.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Design by Nature is a project
we've been doing for 7-8 years.</c>

706ea0d4d77f4a96903895f8cae907c2
00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:28.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A research project.</c>

8de214787068432695b3767cf4c4f477
00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:34.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We talk a lot about how it was
when we were little and were in the forest.</c>

0941bfa819824b7999a5736733eca435
00:18:34.640 --> 00:18:39.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>You behave in a different way
when you're in the forest.</c>

cfd3c87e138f459da55215f9e89dc9c3
00:18:39.240 --> 00:18:45.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Climbing a rock,
and lying down on the ground.</c>

e33041adeb9d41e9beebd72436a5011b
00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:49.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>You get a different movement pattern.</c>

5d7beb3180f947bb9aff671e0adc43a0
00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:58.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We started by going to certain
places we visited many times.</c>

6c31f5732aa74f0cbeaaa3263b675bb0
00:18:59.080 --> 00:19:04.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We came at different times of the year, different
times of the day and in different weather–</c>

bc7d7a14ffd34c91964ab239b3352155
00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:06.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and documented.</c>

53e793ccf8684a8d888da765d411299d
00:19:07.120 --> 00:19:14.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We painted, drew
and photographed a lot.</c>

ae3d3b4fdaaa49bd9851c288e8f04ac5
00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:19.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And we took different textures
we found in nature.</c>

dfc729b31588413e829a9d86c6a665ba
00:19:19.320 --> 00:19:24.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then we scanned 3D
large areas and details.</c>

121e042586c34b5ca3547df20ba88a3a
00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:39.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And we could reform
the 3D files we got–</c>

ff36c1af6c3a49949348ce4aeff5aea8
00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:42.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–into large furniture sculptures–</c>

232ec2a4cfca439eb2f88c31f36aa54d
00:19:42.960 --> 00:19:49.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that we could mill
and make soft furniture.</c>

0939def6ab5843ff816ee9a41cf89921
00:19:57.400 --> 00:20:03.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They have scanned moss, rocks,
plants, lakes, ice and animal tracks.</c>

ab42f06475df4ab29341b76dcd384f09
00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:08.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Front Design mixes 3D technology
with traditional craftsmanship–</c>

b5811c5d5fc8486ca46da014fe8d01bc
00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:12.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–such as plant dyeing,
embroidery and upholstery.</c>

2793d8372b7f48f7ba73e10d43be94a2
00:20:14.560 --> 00:20:20.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>These are upholstered pieces
that we have embroidered.</c>

7649bffe6f3643ad8f42449375bd3322
00:20:20.960 --> 00:20:25.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We thought it was fun
to work with many different techniques.</c>

239ebbf2e3c24d9e98a4b58606b2c575
00:20:25.800 --> 00:20:32.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That also had different tactilities
you discover after a while–</c>

053a30adcc604d57afc524c0fbdf4298
00:20:32.960 --> 00:20:36.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–so it becomes a relief in the fabric.</c>

d846da0265174323a542044c33291c80
00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:44.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>All the figurative is in the fabric.
It's not printed on the cloth.</c>

ca16550732f54282add5c94196ffce85
00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:47.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It's woven.</c>

e29c0894d7fd43f3a1b4e8c4a825b3d7
00:20:56.640 --> 00:21:02.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We wanted it to feel like if
you had taken a handful of the forest–</c>

b9763cbdba8b4da7aec8a8bc44b88119
00:21:02.280 --> 00:21:06.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–taken a piece of the forest
and brought it home.</c>

b9db53f3e4f543aca634f21d9b01ba9e
00:21:38.440 --> 00:21:43.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Front Design has gone against
the prevailing norms–</c>

d27321e1cd40414e90dec081271f3a95
00:21:43.160 --> 00:21:49.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–since they were founded in the early 2000s
about what design and good taste is.</c>

534f06ec8c964d66a522d83d28b64024
00:21:49.200 --> 00:21:54.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>As for example
using figurative language.</c>

e236d4a99c954dc3b24ea6af170b10d8
00:22:04.840 --> 00:22:08.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They had received a commission, a brief:</c>

0754d30a5ee64b7cb79f66fcdff2ac61
00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:12.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>"Make a lamp
that my grandmother would also like."</c>

42e378095466476ebce9d95d2c70b4d9
00:22:13.120 --> 00:22:19.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then it became a horse
with a lamp on its head at 1:1 scale.</c>

0d0a830e6ccf4dee9a1a3cfba0520992
00:22:27.440 --> 00:22:32.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It has been fun to see how people
have reacted to these pieces of furniture.</c>

b12d928eacda4e88b246a0ea8147588c
00:22:33.120 --> 00:22:37.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Some really hated them.</c>

34d34c93a2e743e2bc6ff84b59c33252
00:22:37.800 --> 00:22:41.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–It was so horrible, they thought.
–Yes.</c>

cfebbd614b2f458897e024043c8e687e
00:22:41.280 --> 00:22:44.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It was an offense to make it.</c>

88d4edbcf5e84edaa1599a7fb7c7f234
00:22:44.960 --> 00:22:51.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It was really not allowed
to make things so figurative.</c>

bc82563081c24180bd6d2096f1727124
00:22:51.440 --> 00:22:57.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But it was interesting to see
that people come up and caress it.</c>

0ba9744f87bb414597a055c23846f34c
00:22:57.440 --> 00:23:00.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>People sending images
of when they ride the horse.</c>

8d8188562556415890b88cdad10aee9a
00:23:00.760 --> 00:23:04.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Madonna, Usain Bolt and...</c>

20dfef6953484cb2a83c685320373582
00:23:04.800 --> 00:23:08.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Robbie Williams had it
in their wedding photo.</c>

3af88a2a09344efc98501ca940c014d7
00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:14.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Zlatan Ibrahimovic... They have posted
images of themselves with the horse.</c>

7c4058622b174acf891acd1624a5e12a
00:23:14.760 --> 00:23:17.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It lives many different lives.</c>

6571fb7257424279a108dd804587977
00:23:45.520 --> 00:23:51.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Front Design shook the design world
when in their graduation project–</c>

38031c3f84bf4f1098f43932493cf41a
00:23:52.120 --> 00:23:56.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–they let rats gnaw the pattern
into tapestries–</c>

439807c46745477eadf88dfbe2240471
00:23:56.360 --> 00:24:00.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and snakes form
the everyday object.</c>

dc1fd3bff50545898eb721e22ef8ac65
00:24:02.520 --> 00:24:06.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>If animals make the form,
who is then the designer?</c>

7ae8f7193d12490987f48f754a8b6d2d
00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:14.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Design by Animals was completely new
in Nordic design history.</c>

3cf120aae76d4fa687d73ddcbf61998b
00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:22.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The people didn't understand what we were doing,
I think. They wondered.</c>

8e8ae60d8ecf42ce88ec7125fb278100
00:24:22.560 --> 00:24:25.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Is this design? Why then?</c>

9077afe61c1c47399073e2624c63a911
00:24:25.640 --> 00:24:30.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It was quite far from
the prevailing design scene at that time.</c>

e351dc1570b44b9da90f2588911c5d76
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:34.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This was something
that was more based on a question.</c>

a6204ce4eb8441439e259d74a58cd703
00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:39.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>What is design?
Or what is one as a designer?</c>

bb0af77c28ac44a98c35317c4d81892a
00:24:58.200 --> 00:25:02.160 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>What does craftsmanship
mean in the 2000s?</i></c>

0d6c32be456643e389bd1627c89aa5a
00:25:02.320 --> 00:25:06.640 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>How do we redefine that</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>in a world of mass production?</i></c>

9ec2e3ab83134e61a1d24c338141e2e
00:25:06.800 --> 00:25:10.480 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>What does it mean</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>to make something by hand today?</i></c>

e957df418c5b4c868fbba94f9cdd6ec5
00:25:12.080 --> 00:25:15.480 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Have we also used technology?</i></c>

41b90c8ad5144962978dd1a0eb693299
00:25:15.640 --> 00:25:19.720 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Is it perhaps a mix?</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>It's exciting.</i></c>

31e416570b62478fb8a93e4a9c9cb729
00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:23.240 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Cecilie Manz's focus</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>is on the fragility of materials.</i></c>

d9648b3ba5a84fd394071370baae78b6
00:25:23.400 --> 00:25:27.560 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>The models are of washing paper
in deep tones...</i></c>

01157ddd9abd4c059973012efe1e3626
00:26:22.760 --> 00:26:26.680 align:left position:22%
Can't you make something people want to buy?

41588378adcd46698f074c80d92898a1
00:26:26.840 --> 00:26:30.120 align:left position:22%
Here we have the Fuck You chair.

22d5db679412426d85db609fdeede365
00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:36.800 align:left position:22%
I'm a lightweight.

cba5f3bee9a2441d8fefef1086517091
00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:42.800 align:left position:22%
One draws the same chair all the time.

7048abc109834899b574d2a664e08a3f
00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:47.400 align:left position:22%
One sees the younger ones designing chairs–

531a88f34568428b8aaae8ea0c338f68
00:26:47.560 --> 00:26:52.960 align:left position:22%
–that could be taken from
some 60s magazine. What's the point?

b811d54f6651437981d81890610a0494
00:26:54.240 --> 00:26:58.800 align:left position:22%
In Scandinavian design
it has been almost like a religion.

874d25528f6a496aaa2017a8f038dce4
00:26:58.960 --> 00:27:03.440 align:left position:22%
It becomes boring in the long run,
I think at least.

ea6fd15eefb54e7aadceb635f3011751
00:27:03.600 --> 00:27:08.120 align:left position:22%
When design has become a religion–

db79b5870f724709bc0bf705cc09fd78
00:27:08.280 --> 00:27:12.160 align:left position:22%
–then it's like light wood.

fc3172b515554a3c9a2fd3c248fcb3ee
00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:16.880 align:left position:22%
Design is not a religion,
it's something to have fun with.

2d6aa0180bd643e6bd34652b0c920447
00:27:18.960 --> 00:27:22.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The design of Icelandic Sigurður Gústafsson–</c>

721767cb35714a2ea0c728c2e29363d2
00:27:22.880 --> 00:27:28.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is far from traditionally
Nordic design of clean lines.</c>

f1ee047ebcf74327ab1ed9a7a7bf50ef
00:27:28.520 --> 00:27:33.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His works are based
on childhood games in the dump–</c>

7bcff60ddad84e03a37b7f8dc53355b3
00:27:33.320 --> 00:27:36.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that was close to the childhood home.</c>

455e285602be4f12963c9c5306d4ddcc
00:27:36.960 --> 00:27:41.480 align:left position:22%
As a small child I played a lot among ships.

4756d0510b5b4a12a628e05d8c8b5d98
00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:47.160 align:left position:22%
I lived close to a small harbor
and there were ships everywhere.

645e56fde78a417fab1d6c67368b3ce9
00:27:47.320 --> 00:27:52.840 align:left position:22%
It should be considered as a bad play environment today...

552e6a1b4b724e25a91c372a64d1a8c
00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:59.360 align:left position:22%
I played in the shipyard dump
that still exists in Akureyri.

2b0a1a5717e847aabbfb1c050ff6a419
00:27:59.520 --> 00:28:03.600 align:left position:22%
There I played with all kinds of rubbish.

562664599ab94c7f90d5ee5ccac72771
00:28:14.120 --> 00:28:19.640 align:left position:22%
So arose the name A-Eki.
"A, ekki!" is something you say to children.

4aede7c93d924284a2ff7309d33f442c
00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:23.160 align:left position:22%
"No haga eso!" (Don't do that!)

57386767794f496db99bdbdca60084f6
00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:28.320 align:left position:22%
I never said it to my son,
even though he smeared my things with ice cream.

e76b85df40a046fe9ddbf3ae53cb73f2
00:28:28.480 --> 00:28:31.080 align:left position:22%
My furniture shouldn't be so sensitive.

c10030b389dd49389f552d95c27f915e
00:28:31.240 --> 00:28:37.360 align:left position:22%
I don't understand that furniture
shouldn't be used. What kind of home is that?

ce145c938d284294b2b1fbc70fff51b4
00:28:39.320 --> 00:28:42.240 align:left position:22%
A-Eki is Ikea backwards.

e5341125b8d8484b967e06ea485502ec
00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:58.160 align:left position:22%
In some aspects, some of the chairs
are more sculptures than chairs.

2b8b1674f0c841c88cd35eae150d3305
00:28:58.320 --> 00:29:01.480 align:left position:22%
In my home there are no pictures on the walls.

cd5587ed51fd4e0bb211865901e75ed1
00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:07.800 align:left position:22%
The furniture takes so much attention
that it wouldn't work to have pictures.

8bfdd6c85f6245dfb822d93d51ed485
00:29:09.520 --> 00:29:15.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Sigurður Gústafsson is an architect
trained in Denmark and Norway.</c>

e6bb6bfd087b4a25b3ea0e25234f6e71
00:29:17.320 --> 00:29:22.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The chairs are his way
of playing and relaxing.</c>

64a38cf3655746a6857bb63242cd3d14
00:29:22.480 --> 00:29:27.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That they would succeed
he could never have imagined.</c>

74f43e0f61fe4ff0bca8b837ece9d57c
00:29:27.400 --> 00:29:29.600 align:left position:22%
And then I made the Tango chair.

3eed1f911f254d97af70e552cf4c7c65
00:29:29.760 --> 00:29:33.560 align:left position:22%
Then the cultural section of Jyllands-Posten–

752b0e1e7cc64fe4aaf624e96421c8a0
00:29:33.720 --> 00:29:38.880 align:left position:22%
–covered the entire front page with a photo
of Tango. I was totally blown away.

19af460a5ef441a5a91017af74f5ba42
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:05.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That a chair
doesn't have to be just a chair–</c>

5495e08f6bf9435e852af9d68820cefe
00:30:05.520 --> 00:30:11.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but can equally be a thought,
a question or a daydream–</c>

746cfb22d80d4dd2a15e50568ea1962f
00:30:11.720 --> 00:30:17.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is a red thread in the craft
in the North around the turn of the millennium–</c>

1aa990b916b14f81bb5565461d4b3fe1
00:30:17.920 --> 00:30:21.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–also in Sigurður Gústafsson.</c>

c3b53f36dbd24811abd5f13c4a706f06
00:30:24.040 --> 00:30:28.160 align:left position:22%
I was on vacation in Spain
and my girlfriend was sleeping.

4b3aec59afc94ed6b8c80b63b41b0674
00:30:28.320 --> 00:30:33.400 align:left position:22%
I was watching TV, Clint Eastwood
dubbed into Spanish.

754fb1867b1d48cc9d83f41887818510
00:30:33.560 --> 00:30:37.760 align:left position:22%
I thought: "I'll draw a rocking chair
for Clint Eastwood."

d0c734cbeb0c482f0a826be0d16a1d39
00:30:37.920 --> 00:30:43.600 align:left position:22%
It has to be a cool chair
for such a tough guy. Him and Keith Richards.

8f8e0db477a14a01b2b77903a0439105
00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:49.200 align:left position:22%
So this is a rocking chair
for aging rock stars.

5ed6637a3d3c44f3a15311d602671a4a
00:30:49.360 --> 00:30:53.600 align:left position:22%
It's good for rocking,
it's like a pendulum.

aca593ee50314cfaa6b60835b0f67909
00:31:38.360 --> 00:31:43.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But not all chairs are just play
for Sigurður Gústafsson.</c>

b5814fd3377e490381d1be9e123482b8
00:31:49.640 --> 00:31:53.640 align:left position:22%
This is a chair I made
as a symbol of...

7afe94a872eb4b2288b6a96e9cc2304c
00:31:53.800 --> 00:31:57.040 align:left position:22%
...the Utøya attacks in Norway.

84a0daf5a12341eb926cbf6c56be2e34
00:31:57.200 --> 00:32:00.280 align:left position:22%
This is completely random.

5952d319a83141d1ac73e0b0adc09201
00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:06.520 align:left position:22%
It becomes as it becomes. You take sticks
and put them in slightly different directions.

f1f2903e8d8c469cb9ae6fb7706c3089
00:32:06.680 --> 00:32:12.000 align:left position:22%
They support each other
and then it becomes very strong.

a26230094fb74c4491346cffea5ade82
00:32:12.160 --> 00:32:15.760 align:left position:22%
So the thought here...

77c7ee2a1caa4f8dbd64918e5bb1bc2d
00:32:15.920 --> 00:32:20.360 align:left position:22%
This is what we understand as...

2e9754ca185d4934b41c73bf50afec8c
00:32:20.520 --> 00:32:25.400 align:left position:22%
...the strong, the big buildings we have,
the structure of society.

95618c820a6248acb992718195fc08bc
00:32:25.560 --> 00:32:28.440 align:left position:22%
A bit pretentious for a small chair...

1b51b1998d2f45b5861ceadeee2d04f8
00:32:28.600 --> 00:32:33.040 align:left position:22%
But the strength of society is in the small.

172f7ff3f3a84767a9cf7a80aa11a0d3
00:32:33.200 --> 00:32:36.640 align:left position:22%
What makes us human.

4b64dba26cd2492db4a8365577a68039
00:32:36.800 --> 00:32:40.480 align:left position:22%
Being kind to each other.

d71eaa28f8cd4bb9986eef845e62c8d0
00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:43.720 align:left position:22%
The soft side of the creator.

354cea9d8f684317ab678d1699126c36
00:32:53.280 --> 00:32:57.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The designation what is
Swedish design is so diluted today–</c>

4c0082ffbf5348fea49b85f16a11fa0b
00:32:57.520 --> 00:33:01.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that we must face the legacy
completely correctly.</c>

d6126ed8288a47d88a6065434b37e5b1
00:33:03.400 --> 00:33:08.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In addition to returning to nature
and the DIY punk spirit–</c>

5c4fc1c7f63440ad8bd19b9b62d98958
00:33:08.720 --> 00:33:14.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–the critical question becomes central
under the 2000s design.</c>

37ffc5a9c7394583a87edd7e3071c3a3
00:33:14.480 --> 00:33:20.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The brochure "Ugly and Beautiful". Points out
that not all design is...</c>

6728a407f81e4d30a4786ff365ffec3d
00:33:20.360 --> 00:33:25.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>What is exactly good taste,
and who decides that?</c>

5bdc221101964847b57098feb9cad8f9
00:33:26.680 --> 00:33:30.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The 90s design scene
as I remember it...</c>

c0dce2869c0843d78365a77e994a6a34
00:33:30.840 --> 00:33:35.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The established scenes
were very busy with–</c>

6ca875b069bd4153a720d935fc74117b
00:33:36.120 --> 00:33:42.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–a special history of taste and style
that I didn't recognize.</c>

11bd810669ef4b329f7ed5aa390ec1ec
00:33:42.400 --> 00:33:46.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They talked about quite similar values
and an aesthetic–</c>

6bcc6316e23949c8b192bbfd77524306
00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:53.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–of minimalism, light gray, white
and light wood that was all over.</c>

2982ed94dd5246c6b9a0749dd552e929
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:08.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In my generation I am the designer
who has received the most criticism.</c>

11650e329ec94c549846fe46f1e6d423
00:34:09.120 --> 00:34:15.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>There are few others to whom one has been able
to write everything.</c>

e9d9fc058c5342ce82de9b778fe70f39
00:34:15.840 --> 00:34:21.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It hangs so clearly with
that I myself have said things.</c>

7a5e71782be4495ebd3d24e8de03366c
00:34:21.240 --> 00:34:25.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I put questions
to employees and managers.</c>

6ee8c691e12f4ce093d98353adc63941
00:34:25.680 --> 00:34:30.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I was interested in
that someone would explain to me–</c>

de5be08e97dc4a059b3db4a26c6720ce
00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:37.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–why certain things were considered finer,
more functional and more valuable.</c>

2ef351527712486c8aa0c6c0b939db22
00:34:39.720 --> 00:34:43.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I was interested in what was
noisy, beautiful and sticky–</c>

3de355b705c14f7395ab09eb8266b338
00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:47.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and that had a little girl room aesthetic.</c>

f79669e6b7bf40b6aa0ba1936c48cb77
00:34:48.880 --> 00:34:56.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>My graduation project in 1999,
Beautiful decorative lamps.</c>

bafebdd469d947269acac247cab0490a
00:34:56.640 --> 00:35:01.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And they were made in a technique
where you roll clay–</c>

9de0eaf6362342da94f5987f585d3adc
00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:06.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and it was a technique
that wasn't considered fine or good–</c>

25336ae0374a4160a1649d9044b2937f
00:35:07.080 --> 00:35:12.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–because it doesn't show ceramic skill, which was important then.</c>

d56829bba41d4f40a1649d9044b07510
00:35:13.120 --> 00:35:17.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Have you made this lamp? –Johan,
is this excellent Swedish design?</c>

4da0d407129b4ebcbe8b28db738c48e7
00:35:17.120 --> 00:35:19.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>No, it is not.</c>

e67110c4ae954d2abdbc52f0b60f8e05
00:35:30.640 --> 00:35:36.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>With the rolled lamps Zandra Ahl
gives the book "Ugly and Beautiful"–</c>

30e2dd8c75ae4e44b226b5caa03007b8
00:35:36.960 --> 00:35:43.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–where she describes the Nordic style ideal
as anorexia aesthetics.</c>

2d713b0c9d514377a839dd879ac9bb7
00:35:44.080 --> 00:35:50.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>She is not the only one questioning
taste and purpose of design.</c>

60e18b5431dd46ea916c5b73690c2d23
00:35:53.040 --> 00:35:56.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Around the turn of the millennium
they become more convinced–</c>

439a9229f2e947cbac77ede51edf2cea
00:35:57.000 --> 00:36:01.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that the purpose of design
is to ask critical questions.</c>

2f476b1449564060977f64942f5bcc7c
00:36:05.360 --> 00:36:11.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>We live in a world that drowns
in things, more now than ever.</c>

3d2455a91ed842d7a3aafaaa34ff436e
00:36:11.720 --> 00:36:18.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And reproduces values about
what should be a good life.</c>

d84c4d6fc32944deab702ebd06bb463f
00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:24.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And then using the form itself
to stop and reflect–</c>

9b536631933d49fc9e7b15b44d9fd299
00:36:24.920 --> 00:36:29.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is very interesting, and craft
has a special position there.</c>

7d66b965e5ee4a6480d78bcc890b160e
00:36:29.520 --> 00:36:35.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It can be a vase or a pot,
but also a critical pot.</c>

6224a768d13a4de39abd9e15a78ead7e
00:36:43.280 --> 00:36:48.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>She wanted to change the world.
No young woman should be ashamed.</c>

678ad7a9369147d19d27186289720cf7
00:36:48.600 --> 00:36:54.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>One should not be able to discard aesthetics
and taste. It has been all.</c>

77d3ce8d137a41b29331fea9ae7bfab5
00:37:12.240 --> 00:37:15.520 align:left position:22%
We design the light ourselves.

af1558a0707f4503b0df1567fab8adf6
00:37:15.680 --> 00:37:20.040 align:left position:22%
The difference is
that now we have dynamic elements.

5764505df5a24365ba355e3ed4d087a8
00:37:23.480 --> 00:37:30.120 align:left position:22%
This Nordic...the sunlight.

f197d413323f4bfdb483d635e0f92a4a
00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:36.120 align:left position:22%
One must get it exactly right
for the illusion to work.

30953349611a4c40bb963dcdd36a45c7
00:37:36.280 --> 00:37:39.320 align:left position:22%
–Very nice.
–Thank you.

016fa59978f94dde99c576ed0d16de23
00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:05.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Who has exactly decided that
a lamp must look like a lamp?</c>

2b5e0b720d76471c861167bac2eb471e
00:38:07.680 --> 00:38:12.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And how does it affect humans
different types of light?</c>

4d07bc015744418e86a582d7ef8c61a9
00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:17.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>These are the questions
in Daniel Rybakken's design–</c>

f5157fe1afef428890eb2a5f955c5621
00:38:17.760 --> 00:38:24.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that have led him to create a
lamp that doesn't look like a lamp.</c>

3dc58e7b3b4143d3862d0a502b60fb5c
00:38:30.720 --> 00:38:37.440 align:left position:22%
The project became a lamp that looks
like an abstraction of a blind.

53a47b581133490ba507ea87d184dedf
00:38:37.600 --> 00:38:44.480 align:left position:22%
It is an aluminum plate with a tube,
and then I have worked with the light around–

5a58482806164f72be8a6bc1045d6e80
00:38:44.640 --> 00:38:52.640 align:left position:22%
–that shines out of the lamp's form
on the wall around and on the floor below.

c53dc7a10ea84167bf8391b0150769e5
00:38:57.320 --> 00:39:00.160 align:left position:22%
This actually started with this.

b2d292b5e49b4bcb9f318331d7167519
00:39:00.320 --> 00:39:04.040 align:left position:22%
I began making lamps that gave–

5123c607b1f34f92b70a9eb342c98bd4
00:39:04.200 --> 00:39:08.520 align:left position:22%
–an illusion of direct sunlight
shining in.

d3e61ed9202f48efb3afee5a3dd50dda
00:39:13.600 --> 00:39:19.080 align:left position:22%
The feeling that was created
by having natural sunlight–

c5c7fbc3b0c24f188ee566c3896a841e
00:39:19.240 --> 00:39:24.280 align:left position:22%
–was that one was somehow
part of what is outside the room.

45829371d5ad4714a6132c2c36799d72
00:39:24.440 --> 00:39:28.360 align:left position:22%
When that was changed
to artificial light–

1386365c312943c0877a077d46686ab5
00:39:28.520 --> 00:39:34.600 align:left position:22%
–it was like a prison,
like being locked in a cell.

7029903427b04d7b9dd487c598b683dd
00:39:55.640 --> 00:40:00.200 align:left position:22%
My relationship with light
started when I was little.

9bb94629cc914c7e958d62feab938043
00:40:00.360 --> 00:40:07.280 align:left position:22%
Like many others in the North
I am sensitive to light–

2ae8031f507b4d78938596d71cc0f8c3
00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:13.160 align:left position:22%
–especially when winter comes
with the long dark periods.

ead32e1cf5ad43268783879a509f170b
00:40:13.320 --> 00:40:18.480 align:left position:22%
I began to wonder
why it affected us.

0ccef168e92d49d388cdde6ad6a95e03
00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:22.320 align:left position:22%
Is it just...

20d6c7144cb74631b935026de7fc73b8
00:40:22.480 --> 00:40:27.120 align:left position:22%
...the medical,
or is there something more?

eb492b1a6cb94366b9d1b7adb7263d98
00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:31.080 align:left position:22%
What I saw and began to think was–

218f7d52cc9e4a68ba302fb51eb5f565
00:40:31.240 --> 00:40:37.680 align:left position:22%
–that in a room
where one receives natural sunlight–

deeeebc535484915a5740c41b083789d
00:40:37.840 --> 00:40:42.960 align:left position:22%
–one is somehow
part of what is outside the room.

c7a7ed4a5e3a4e5db499a50ca2c5b960
00:40:44.960 --> 00:40:50.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>These reflections become the breakthrough
of Daniel Rybakken as a designer.</c>

85f07834423e42139a068c909a0c1ce2
00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:06.760 align:left position:22%
My first project was called
<c.urfjarran><i>The subconscious effect of daylight.</i></c>

e7666c3fb55b4db9aec0d230ddb29e91
00:41:06.920 --> 00:41:11.280 align:left position:22%
It was about
the sunlight coming in.

3f93d8f0820c4cfd9bdf7eadc849cf7
00:41:11.440 --> 00:41:15.200 align:left position:22%
In Sweden they have a good word, "sun cat".

a1ca1bc6fc4046759a25e2fc148d2910
00:41:16.600 --> 00:41:22.360 align:left position:22%
One can project light
from a projector on the floor–

6e76b302d72146b48ae2cf1025789d56
00:41:22.520 --> 00:41:25.200 align:left position:22%
–but where to hide the projector?

70de31c05fdc4a6387140663af51352c
00:41:25.360 --> 00:41:30.320 align:left position:22%
That was my first encounter
with Milan and the fair.

31e1f10432474bb5b7b8646bcdbffc5d
00:41:30.480 --> 00:41:34.200 align:left position:22%
The reactions were really incredible.

e495b3f8f2944151a7586c820e20a659
00:41:34.360 --> 00:41:41.760 align:left position:22%
People in suits lay on the floor
and looked under the table.

cde3fcd0f3a443c0be205d2d8af53580
00:41:41.920 --> 00:41:44.720 align:left position:22%
That was the start of my career.

9432d181f42c434f82df5ebace4d0d78
00:41:47.080 --> 00:41:52.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A lamp in the shape of a sun cat
hits the design world.</c>

b4972d6add1a44c19857ec8a8e1f71d6
00:41:53.600 --> 00:41:59.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But the sun cat is also a critique
of the conservative industry.</c>

79fb5d20bb0a46f3b914044e1f9a60dd
00:42:00.840 --> 00:42:06.120 align:left position:22%
My critique was that we still
designed lamps in the same way.

863867bf0f13467095841d389adc5290
00:42:06.280 --> 00:42:12.760 align:left position:22%
Why did we design lamp shades
without thinking about the light effect?

d15c7de8e45d48e7882f60fdef1a5c58
00:42:16.800 --> 00:42:19.480 align:left position:22%
It was quite conservative.

7a8b5dcc25b74bab817e4f755b869b71
00:42:19.640 --> 00:42:27.480 align:left position:22%
There were different types of lamp:
the hanging, the wall and the work.

55466135efbb4f2bb75da71ff1fc6dbc
00:43:17.600 --> 00:43:24.600 align:left position:22%
At the same time there are examples of people
who have worked more with light.

15dd1268eaca44af93fcc272d4fd45bd
00:43:24.760 --> 00:43:29.280 align:left position:22%
Look at the PH lamps for example.

95ae2fe4da0345f9b0816576e0e9c4f6
00:43:29.440 --> 00:43:34.600 align:left position:22%
It is an elegant thin screen,
but it fulfills a function.

5a14c46571d5412b946fa70d66fa0739
00:43:34.760 --> 00:43:40.120 align:left position:22%
It is about
how light is reflected in the lamp.

b38b842ebaef47609440eede906ae910
00:43:56.520 --> 00:44:02.720 align:left position:22%
We are programmed in the North...

8243457d4ee1409794e3ff9cd04c94ae
00:44:02.880 --> 00:44:05.880 align:left position:22%
...to feel that light is positive.

d05199fb35254c368524046874ffa62b
00:44:27.520 --> 00:44:33.000 align:left position:22%
The lamp as an object has an important role.

89245b8e435e4f5a9af776eab2f5f15a
00:44:33.160 --> 00:44:37.560 align:left position:22%
It is about
having an element–

53cfabada2f246e4ab1e4cdaede31e45
00:44:37.720 --> 00:44:42.640 align:left position:22%
–that perhaps contributes
to a poetic touch.

5b024b80d56b4bd6bb6da6377ac84508
00:44:47.400 --> 00:44:51.640 align:left position:22%
So I think the lamp as an object–

5fc55775fb1544f997be9aeeaa086922
00:44:51.800 --> 00:44:57.000 align:left position:22%
–is something
we will continue to value.

d9214d63c98647c38196aa0a4f088dd9
00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:14.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But not all contemporary designers
have questions–</c>

a89acbda7db349d4b234b23a69e9aefc
00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:17.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–in every object they make.</c>

2f5bc82d0c6c4d82bb65de6aed50499d
00:45:17.920 --> 00:45:23.400 align:left position:22%
I wanted to make a chair
that was just a chair.

94aa59467c0b4b988da5cb3b3b4809c3
00:45:23.560 --> 00:45:28.480 align:left position:22%
Solid and something one dares
to grab hard.

b883ed0757ba42beb24b9caa82a26ef8
00:45:28.640 --> 00:45:36.640 align:left position:22%
When I was offered to design a chair for Svinkløv,
I said: "There are already fine chairs."

0e61ef5d458f4fbfbb9a76914f88ce3f
00:45:36.800 --> 00:45:41.040 align:left position:22%
"We produce already too much
in the world."

f70eddb135c6493da92a661341ce4338
00:45:41.200 --> 00:45:46.280 align:left position:22%
We are producing already too much
here in the world.

0c96c41260344cf9a5b53bf91a05588c
00:45:46.440 --> 00:45:52.960 align:left position:22%
We must begin to think about what we have
around and what we reproduce.

4d08783e07c34a5a922a3aeb2d21573c
00:45:53.120 --> 00:45:58.720 align:left position:22%
It has always been a paradox for me
being in a production industry.

aeeebd7fb5434149be0528f00f7d2407
00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:02.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Chris Halstrøm is traditional–</c>

0b76c5237f2f437392838af8f8ca07a3
00:46:02.560 --> 00:46:08.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and works side by side
with ancient Nordic masters.</c>

010d0245286b4b8aab6e283f3bfef802
00:46:09.360 --> 00:46:12.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>So perhaps it is not strange
that he got the commission–</c>

eda7885a67ee4f3fa98db96ebb3d3f12
00:46:13.120 --> 00:46:20.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to create a chair for the beloved
century-old spa hotel Svinkløv–</c>

a6820f635387466d9a99b43753219acb
00:46:20.320 --> 00:46:24.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that was completely destroyed in a fire in 2016.</c>

cfa063c085184fc79eebd795647c8b5d
00:46:26.840 --> 00:46:32.000 align:left position:22%
It was interesting to relate
to a building that no longer existed–

7cc45f859910468f9e9fce47245105cc
00:46:32.160 --> 00:46:36.800 align:left position:22%
–but that had meant so much
to so many.

5bd7613bb41c432d8da660bc516b3f8c
00:46:43.800 --> 00:46:48.000 align:left position:22%
Then we have this handle.

f8f1cd28b1204b53be02ed3fb88275f9
00:46:48.160 --> 00:46:53.320 align:left position:22%
In a restaurant one might want
to pull the chair towards the others–

286214c0c39d413b8a250539e92bda2
00:46:53.480 --> 00:46:57.920 align:left position:22%
–if one ever feels like
being a bit friendly.

41bd044828e0464586a250539e92bda2
00:47:00.320 --> 00:47:03.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Working in the shadow
of the Nordic masters–</c>

619bf133f9424422af5c221d269acf8c
00:47:03.880 --> 00:47:07.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–has never been oppressive
for Chris Halstrøm.</c>

0c13f44d84ae4689b0414367d798e173
00:47:07.480 --> 00:47:11.320 align:left position:22%
I have never thought it was heavy.

20f497ffdfb6421eb0db192d296b8b7c
00:47:11.480 --> 00:47:15.640 align:left position:22%
On the contrary.
It is interesting to see how they did.

07d1ceecfa2846298dd10d2d7e434d8b
00:47:15.800 --> 00:47:23.440 align:left position:22%
Like something Kaare Klint did...
It is called "the father of Danish design".

ec335b5378ab45e1b10dc45816c3df08
00:47:25.000 --> 00:47:29.320 align:left position:22%
He was so meticulous,
and it is inspiring.

1d8df3f3cbac412f8688ca80aa11a0d2
00:47:29.480 --> 00:47:33.800 align:left position:22%
Be meticulous with what you work with.

2a7c1c602fe747c79f7d041d701b7fc1
00:47:33.960 --> 00:47:40.160 align:left position:22%
No matter if you are a furniture designer,
mechanic or air traffic controller.

4c76738a96994dd195fd460c6004840
00:47:40.320 --> 00:47:43.400 align:left position:22%
Be meticulous with what you do.

f3827d512115428eb0fba530afe23856
00:47:43.560 --> 00:47:48.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And meticulous was also
the Finnish designer Alvar Aalto.</c>

51d460bf674546168f3d0648e5916381
00:47:53.920 --> 00:47:59.040 align:left position:22%
I have tattooed the Aaltopöytä
on my arm.

d01b6b5996e246a6b54cf24bc0c530af
00:47:59.200 --> 00:48:04.520 align:left position:22%
It is a good example of
what good design can be.

173d937ee22c4459ab562abceb8a41ab
00:48:04.680 --> 00:48:11.600 align:left position:22%
It is sculptural, functional and durable.
And it does what it should.

dc9b74ebaa1442cd961ba50f46fa4870
00:49:21.760 --> 00:49:25.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In the ancient industrial city Fiskars
in southwestern Finland–</c>

efe5d0bb0a034dcb8d676aeb9542eff3
00:49:25.960 --> 00:49:31.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–iron and steel production has been changed
to design and craftsmanship.</c>

751fb9bd1e68410d91724de6f4faea02
00:49:36.320 --> 00:49:42.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And in a factory where leaf springs for trucks were produced–</c>

b845e905de834578a3d0a13620e8c11b
00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:48.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–birch cast cabinets and wooden mushrooms
are now manufactured.</c>

dcbdfaf37c8b45f1894b97e40e3fda77
00:49:51.720 --> 00:49:58.640 align:left position:22%
It feels natural for me to challenge
the wood. It stands out in many works.

763a8cdf922b4dfea88a0c6ea35bbc88
00:50:12.080 --> 00:50:16.840 align:left position:22%
I want to see how much
I can process the wood...

28823cdea4884a2c809d93d696c4fd8e
00:50:18.640 --> 00:50:24.000 align:left position:22%
...so that it is still reasonable
to work with it–

09ddc47be1ff4a52bc5b4b696ca09944
00:50:24.160 --> 00:50:28.400 align:left position:22%
–and so that it looks
like a natural material.

0567d95748cc4390a38067498505ff05
00:50:52.200 --> 00:50:59.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Antrei Hartikainen's craft follows
the seasons in the Finnish nature.</c>

19fa6c9ecb7c47608dbcd71330c07e69
00:51:03.720 --> 00:51:09.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Among other things the Melt series
twists in different materials.</c>

9d6541ca101442a991e57943f3602ca0
00:51:10.120 --> 00:51:17.200 align:left position:22%
His source of inspiration
is the winter transforming into spring–

a9f9e0c32eca4e738aa083499dc13f24
00:51:17.360 --> 00:51:25.000 align:left position:22%
–when the sun makes the ice melt fast
and water flows underneath.

9d2bd86914204cf68f94f506cbad7e96
00:51:25.160 --> 00:51:32.880 align:left position:22%
The light reflections on the ice surface
are seen in the glass.

cbced044feb5465c879e6cd6ab12340f
00:51:58.120 --> 00:52:00.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is in the nature around Fiskars–</c>

3a68488e0aef45efb81f63f583d1c1a2
00:52:00.800 --> 00:52:05.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–where Antrei Hartikainen
finds ideas for his design.</c>

678b19e98a1d446b8685c1c8816aa3f8
00:52:06.000 --> 00:52:10.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Light and shadows
filtering between tree trunks–</c>

5296b1fd6bf2440a922cbabb8f509537
00:52:10.240 --> 00:52:16.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–transform in his workshop
into award-winning Finnish design.</c>

bd8ab47151ab42c4a5b3c34689e2a7d9
00:52:20.360 --> 00:52:26.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The inspiration for the Bastone series
came from a walk in the forest.</c>

5d370641f05145e8a30aea559d51d230
00:52:28.440 --> 00:52:32.720 align:left position:22%
One sees old, tall tree trunks...

0bde9bcc989143a3abdbfe3e6a70c3c1
00:52:32.880 --> 00:52:37.440 align:left position:22%
In a forest that has been cared for to some extent–

f3ceb0b67de64d34a1f58d629ff1f3a8
00:52:37.600 --> 00:52:41.080 align:left position:22%
–the sunlight filters through.

4f8a204549524130aac3de5ecdd0ac8e
00:52:41.240 --> 00:52:45.080 align:left position:22%
When the low vegetation is not so high–

47e89201017c453ca5922e8d81b8934e
00:52:45.240 --> 00:52:52.360 align:left position:22%
–the forest atmosphere
filters through some light.

db0047ba861247789e6a30861b192caf
00:53:06.920 --> 00:53:13.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>As a teenager Antrei
spent his free time in his father's furniture workshop.</c>

b4eeec4bbb4540a99a8bc481bb282b41
00:53:13.840 --> 00:53:19.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Among tools and different types of wood
his curiosity grew.</c>

da15dcb6dfdc488e9ab9fc3de4de0edf
00:53:19.360 --> 00:53:21.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And when he received a book–</c>

8fd4c0624d304238bcb029d3e3d79bf0
00:53:22.000 --> 00:53:28.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–about the Finnish designer
Tapio Wirkkala, he was hooked.</c>

7d12d707136b4ef2bb50db42b0905b45
00:53:29.480 --> 00:53:37.800 align:left position:22%
Tapio Wirkkala is a person
who has influenced my own work a lot.

c933d4a87c9f49ad9e66b260572d55fc
00:53:37.960 --> 00:53:43.080 align:left position:22%
He always listened attentively to nature–

2b219e256fb747c9cadc2015bd1f1b921
00:53:43.240 --> 00:53:49.560 align:left position:22%
–and was in northern Finland
gathering inspiration–

e8201c02b2054ab283a0f353d23587c6
00:53:49.720 --> 00:53:56.000 align:left position:22%
–from how nature changes
and how seasonal changes affect.

bd11a9f55d2e45e5b706489bb9647511
00:53:56.160 --> 00:54:01.880 align:left position:22%
It plays an important role
also in my own work.

e6e6f6a99a82480da38efeac3cc1c050
00:54:30.800 --> 00:54:37.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Antrei works on the boundary
between art and carpentry.</c>

caa448aa9a0847d3b8edf16321e9699f
00:54:40.560 --> 00:54:46.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The thin mushrooms and flowers
are all hand-carved.</c>

bc95fee58eef42c9a0aabe0b9b491b7e
00:54:46.240 --> 00:54:52.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A laborious work that easily
can end up with the sculpture breaking.</c>

4f8cc277d61f44c19378aec8ca5db619
00:55:06.880 --> 00:55:13.600 align:left position:22%
My work process includes
an element of danger.

2d8b1993d6e94d859f5dd6bfa77687ec
00:55:13.760 --> 00:55:20.680 align:left position:22%
I usually work
quite carefully and step by step.

202b693fe3a7458b87a6a57379048bb8
00:55:22.000 --> 00:55:25.720 align:left position:22%
The wood work is rewarding–

be7e91ff3ce1406d9c807cd9ffafc366
00:55:25.880 --> 00:55:31.000 align:left position:22%
–in that one can
remove a little material at a time.

cfd7370a905744f58a6090606d52fb4b
00:55:34.960 --> 00:55:38.880 align:left position:22%
The sense of the hand is important.

f47b6d3bee2e43678bc123e22b6ca080
00:55:39.040 --> 00:55:46.240 align:left position:22%
One must be able to feel the material and
how much more can be removed from it.

aeef60649ec64f1fafdeba521bc711ed
00:55:50.280 --> 00:55:54.680 align:left position:22%
And then there is the visual element–

5dc6560c288d47f59b7fca3fb85e615a
00:55:54.840 --> 00:55:59.480 align:left position:22%
–which was the original thought.

dbbdfebb045145c48f3505a9252b7fcd
00:56:20.360 --> 00:56:27.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>If the seaweed lamp, the stone chair,
the bark vase, the mushroom lamp–</c>

65ae615a9a884c739d1e016d3c5993f8
00:56:27.240 --> 00:56:30.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–or the sunbeams
under the blind–</c>

b8d9c30f473c43b197755b30bf0b078e
00:56:30.480 --> 00:56:35.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–will become collectibles
in the future remains to be seen.</c>

0ef83e7383fd420380f9a9a06ce68b0d
00:56:42.520 --> 00:56:49.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But they are part of a hundred-year story
about Nordic design–</c>

29faf93d87254675a3d877c3e77a792f
00:56:49.400 --> 00:56:53.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and why it looks the way it does.</c>

d782540faa4645608e8cef822bc461e4
00:56:59.520 --> 00:57:05.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Like the Paimio armchair that makes
tuberculous people breathe freely.</c>

50b183429c6a40fca7d82c9ae1706310
00:57:05.360 --> 00:57:09.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Or the Luxo lamp
with its directed work light.</c>

878f8be64a2045c3abab30f32b147a7b
00:57:11.320 --> 00:57:17.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The Bastu chairs are still pulled out
when political negotiations get stuck.</c>

48e37689b56f4e9bb5b3f16aa3d41db2
00:57:17.760 --> 00:57:22.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And Living Tower
makes conversations reach new heights.</c>

37925bafbd9a49868743fc13e0acce7f
00:57:24.800 --> 00:57:29.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This is a series
about a hundred years of Nordic design–</c>

805de9d27daf4fb4bb912754df3ae720
00:57:29.840 --> 00:57:33.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and why it looks the way it does.</c>

